      <chapter>
      <title>2. Unemployment</title>
        <paragraph>
          Taxes are rising, and unemployment remains at 25%, and near 50% for those aged 18-24.
          Capital controls, including a measure limiting bank withdrawals to €420 a week, are still
          in place. To solve the government is moving to privatise ports, airports and other public
          assets: measures that, while economically sensible, are deeply unpopular.
        </paragraph>
      </chapter>
      <graph unit="%" x="​string" y="number">
