          <chapter>
          <title>What’s the rating system</title>
            <paragraph>
              A credit rating is an evaluation of the credit worthiness of a debtor (a business company or a government)
              predicting the debtor’s ability to pay back the debt. The credit rating represents the evaluation of the
              credit rating agency of qualitative and quantitative information for the debtor.
            </paragraph>
